In this article, President Trump discusses the current state of Obamacare and the need for a replacement plan. He believes that Obamacare is collapsing and in bad shape, and that if they wait two years, it will totally implode. He expresses his support for the replacement plan released by the House of Representatives, which he believes will be more popular and understood than people can imagine. He emphasizes that the new plan will lower costs, expand choices, increase competition, and ensure healthcare access for all Americans. President Trump also mentions the upcoming tax cut plan, but states that they can't move forward with it until they take care of healthcare. He concludes by thanking the Deputy Whip team for their support and expressing his confidence in the success of the new healthcare plan.